                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/stripe/edit/master/knpu/ep2-subscriptions/subscription-renewal-webhook.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>The second webhook <em>type</em> we need to handle is called <code>invoice.payment_succeeded</code>.
This one fires when a subscription is successfully <em>renewed</em>. Well, actually,
it fires whenever <em>any</em> invoice is paid, but we'll sort that out later.</p>
<p>This webhook is important to us for 2 reasons.</p>
<p>First, each subscription has a <code>$billingPeriodEndsAt</code> value that we use to show the
user when Stripe will charge them next:</p>
