</p>
<p>I won't test this - let's call that homework for you - but now whenever a subscription
is renewed, the <code>$billingPeriodEndsAt</code> will be updated.</p>
<h2 id="sending-an-email-on-renewal">Sending an Email on Renewal <a class="headerlink" href="subscription-renewal-webhook#sending-an-email-on-renewal" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>But there's just <em>one</em> other small important thing you'll want to do each time a
subscription is renewed: send the user an email! Ok, we're not <em>actually</em> going
to code up the email-sending logic now - but it would live right here in <code>SubscriptionHelper</code>.</p>
<p>But wait! There is one gotcha: the <code>invoice.payment_succeeded</code> webhook will be triggered
when a subscription is renewed... but it will <em>also</em> be triggered at the moment that
the user <em>originally</em> buys their subscription. So if you send your user an email
that says: "thanks for renewing your subscription", then any new users will be pretty
confused.</p>
<p>To fix this, add a new <code>$isRenewal</code> variable set to
<code>$newPeriodEnd &gt; $subscription-&gt;getBillingPeriodEndsAt()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="652f40364e">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-93" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            93 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="src/AppBundle/Subscription/SubscriptionHelper.php">src/AppBundle/Subscription/SubscriptionHelper.php</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-expandable" data-range="1-8" data-last="0">
                <i class="fa fa-arrows-v js-icon-load-more" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show Lines" data-placement="left"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </td>
